        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 3:00PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 300 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hereford, or 43 miles northeast of Greeley, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grover, Hereford and Pawnee Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
